> will most developer just use TextScaler.textScaleFactor to migrate the app

Yeah unfortunately that's probably going to be the case. 

> what is the long term goal for this property

I think we'll be able to deprecate the property. Apps that target Android U shouldn't use it (although it may take a lot of time and effort to migrate away from it, so I'm not sure what the best time to add the Deprecated annotation for that getter is). Apps that don't target Android U could just assume linear text scaling and do something like this:

```dart
extension LinearScaling on TextScaler { 
  double get textScaleFactor => scale(14.0)/14.0;
} 
```
